                            <comment id="250851" author="adilger" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2019 18:58:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, looking at patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33422&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33422&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11556&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test 32b crashes on MDT umount with &#8220;ASSERTION( atomic_read(&amp;amp;d-&amp;gt;ld_ref) == 0 ) failed: Refcount is 1&#8221;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11556&quot;&gt;LU-11556&lt;/a&gt; tests: fix set_persistent_param_and_check breakage&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it isn&apos;t clear that this introduced the problem that you describe.  It was just fixing a problem where &quot;&lt;tt&gt;$node&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; was being passed to &lt;tt&gt;set_persistent_param_and_check()&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;$facet&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, it doesn&apos;t do anything related to starting/stopping the MGS device?  Is there some other patch that introduced this breakage, or am I missing the connection?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="243016" author="aboyko" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2019 13:06:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only skipping for 32xx at&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/33589&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/33589&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="242536" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2019 18:45:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see you are resolving this with&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/33589.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/33589.&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Why the separate ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
